Police used rubber bullets to disperse the attackers. JOHANNESBURG - A large group of people, suspected to be foreign nationals, pounced on police in the Johannesburg CBD on Sunday. Police used rubber bullets to disperse the attackers. READ: NY police arrest man allegedly planning Times Square attack Gauteng Police Commissioner Elias Mawela says attacking police officers is a serious offence and perpetrators will face the full might of the law. Members of the SAPS and JMPD were on a crime prevention raid in the area, following information about counterfeit goods. The number of people injured or arrested still hasn't been confirmed.